Since the first episode of the remake of iconic TV drama series, ‘The Village Headmaster’ premiered on Sunday, April 29, 2022, it has continue to attract commendation by millions of viewers, including the elderly who watched the original production which aired between 1968 and 1988, and younger generations, who seem to have fallen in love with it based on its artful storytelling, performances, and production. According to a statement by the show’s producers sent to Saturday Beats, the drama series, which was revived through a ground-breaking partnership between the Nigerian Television Authority and Wale Adenuga Productions, is being ‘produced in line with international best practices, and contains the precise volume of suspense, culture, romance, comedy and action, which are the major elements of a great TV series’. Recall that the series parades some members of its original cast, including Dejumo Lewis (Kabiyesi), Ibidun Allison (Amebo), Dan Imoudu (Chief Dagbolu), Dele Osawe (Teacher Fadele), Melville Obriango (Teacher Oghene), Kate Adepegba (Folake), and Lara Akinsola (Doyin); as well as a other actors such as Jide Kosoko, Rachel Oniga, Mr Macaroni, 9ice, Mr Latin, Jide Alabi, Jumoke Odetola, Rykardo Agbor, Ronke Oshodi-Oke, Mide Martins and Omo Ibadan. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com